title: Prawdzik leads Clippesr to victory over Tigers
text:
Prawdzik leads Clippesr to victory over Tigers By: Uncredited Report Error 
Mitchel Prawdzik completed six of 10 passes for 95 yards and a touchdown and ran for two more majors as the Dauphin Clippers defeated the host Neepawa Tigers 37-12 in the Rural Manitoba Football League on Friday. 
Mitchell Popiel caught the nine-yard touchdown pass, while Zac Eiffert rushed for 58 yards on five carries as well as two touchdowns in the nine-man high school game. Daniel Thacker led the Clippers (3-1) on defence with 11 tackles and two assists, while Layton Demchuk had six tackles, four assists, a forced fumble and a knockdown. 
Will Rainka rushed for 118 yards, including an 82-yard gallop to the end zone, for Neepawa (2-2). Will Birnie made nine tackles. 
At Shoal Lake, Anthony Byskal ran for 88 yards and two touchdowns as the Parkwest Outlaws topped the Southwest Sabres 21-16. He also made nine tackles on defence. Corbin Chuhai completed six of 13 passes for 51 yards for the Outlaws (3-1). Logan Byskal added five tackles. 
Kyle Campion completed seven of 13 passes for 220 yards, including a touchdown toss to Kyle Billon, who finished the game with 170 receiving yards for Southwest (1-3). Adam Kowalchuk led the ground charge with 58 yards, and Chaz Will made nine tackles and recovered a fumble. 
Meanwhile, the Swan Valley Tigers improved to 4-0 with a 73-0 win over the East Parkland Warriors (0-4).
